\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 I feel very proud though - though, because I only went to a Cornish school here in Mo
usehole, I have a grandson who had the chance of getting into {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Oxford{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, St Catherine's College, John Pender.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Well I was born in this house and I was seventy-eight last - last Tuesday, the eleventh of January, so I've lived here - all my life.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 You've never moved away from here at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No. I wouldn't know the first thing about moving.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Oh, I had - my brother was the eldest, and he died - Christmas week, he was ninety-one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 What was his name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 William James George. And my - and I had two sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No - older than I, and - my second sister was ten years and a half older than I, and the - and no childr
en between. So there was the four of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 So how old was the oldest of the two sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 My - eldest sister was - seventy-eight when she died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Which was when?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 About eleven years ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 How old was your father when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Oh goodness I can't tell you that, I can't - I should think he was about forty-six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Can you work it out from when he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 My - my father died when he was ninety-four. And he died the - the month the - year the war ended. The two boys came hom
e on leave - from the Army, and - he died while they were home, they - they were - I think all the men had the - had a months holiday I believe after the war ended, so they had to go back, and - they - and wait for demob, you see. And - he died - while th
ey were home, so that would be - the year the war ended.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did he come from Mousehole, was he a Mousehole man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Oh yes. Yes. Yes, he came with his family - there'}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7079132\charrsid3212931 
s - five generations in Mouseho}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 le.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 What was his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Fisherman. Fishing all
 his life. But it - but he was a great scholar, he should have been born - in later years he had - wonderful - brain, and a great reader, and then when he was seventy-five and he finished on the sea, he commenced to paint. And - he had - painted hundreds 
of pictures and - well gave them away to young people who were getting married, they'd all come and ask for a picture, and - they're all over the world, his pictures. An Austr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7079132\charrsid3212931 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 an couple that - came here to live, they put on - on - they had a gallery of pictures called t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7079132\charrsid3212931 he Art Gallery here in Mousehole}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931  and they invited - me to bring his pictures down and have a - exhibition, and we could have sold them all. We collected forty-five then, here in the village. And what we had ourselves you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did your father have any part time jobs or casual work or was he purely a fisherman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
Oh no, that was a full time job in those days. Because - was only the latter years of the sea going that they had engines on the boat. It was all done by sail and - rowing, and 
- the - the fishermen mostly here, they - they didn't own the boats, they - they had the - so many nets each - on the boat you see and the - and the gear and - so - they had to - to look after their gear in the spare time and - they was kept busy mending 
t
he nets and getting others ready - to go on the next season, and in this day of fishing they were - going from one port to another - from Scarborough to - to - Scotland, and from Scotland to Ireland, and - from Ireland to the Isle of Man, but practically 
a
ll - most of their time was - was spent on different course fishing, different - fish, mackerel or herring as the case may be, and - so by the time they came home, in each season they - they perhaps were home for a few weeks, that'd take them all their ti
me then getting the other - gear ready. And I've heard 'em say so often, he - he was - cook - for - for seven men on a boat when he was only ten. And he - yes, he must have been more aggravation he said.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 How old was he when he went on the boats?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
Ten years old. Well I - he was younger than that when they went fishing, well then all the boys here in the village he said would go when they were seven or eight. You can hardly credit it now can you? Just like boys going on the mine, going down the mine
 and that. Sent at a very early age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 So I don't suppose he'd ever have been out of work at all then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
No, no, no, the - and - the - the worst time of the year was this - was the winter when they came home from Plymouth, and they would go up to Pl
ymouth and be there perhaps about sixteen weeks. Go up - in the - the latter part of November sometime and they wouldn't be able to afford to come home, not very often. Sometimes if they struck luck they may come home for Christmas and - I rem - I - I've 
k
nown my father to sell a net - to come home and spend Christmas home with the family. And then - the - the - the worst time of the year really was after Christmas when they came home, between the - winter season and the spring season. And it seems to me -
 
by what - what weather we have lately that - we had harder winters then than what they are now. Colder and - seemed to be more wind, they couldn't go to sea, but whether it was because, they had sailing boats - and they didn't have the help that they have
 now. But there was a long lapse between the - winter season and the spring season - which would perhaps be nearly April, before, and the fi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7079132\charrsid3212931 sher wives and the families dre}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 aded that part of the year, more than anything else. And the - the wives had to be ver
y careful - on their money, if they - if they got - a few pounds, and - lots of times I've asked my mother for a new coat or dress or something I thought I would want, and - she would say, well, I can't afford it now. And - I would say instantly, well fat
h
er got some so - a few weeks ago you see. And - the reply would be, yes, and it may be months before they get anything more. And of course there was no unemployment. And they had to depend on the shops - to help them, and - they - they were very good, the
 
- the shops then was always kept by - by village people, who understood the fishing, and they knew the people that they were dealing with, see, and if the - if they allowed - families - weeks or - or to three months of the year to have credit, they knew t
hat as soon as the money was - was got they would have it back. And that's how - people lived in the days that - are passed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Do you know how old your mother was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No, I'm sorry about that, I should have I suppose, I think she wa
s about - I should reckon she was about thirty - five or six. Because there was ten years now difference in my - second sister and I you see. And my father was eight years older than mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7079132\charrsid3212931 Was she a Mousehole}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931  girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes. Oh yes, our families ar
e - one of the earliest families in the - in the register in church, Poole church. Her name was Mann. Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did she ever work before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No, only helping her father who had a - they had - her father had - two or three brothers,
 and they had three boats, and - she helped with the - all the nets, making - they used to make their own nets then, and - and what I've heard her - say she was kept busy - helping with the nets and - breed them, they used to breed the nets and do everyth
ing by them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 What do you mean breed the nets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Make - make them and - put on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7079132\charrsid3212931 losels}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931  and the - put line and fix them all up for them, and - then they would have the job of - of knitting - the men's - sweaters, which was done then on eight steel
 needles, fairly fine needles, and fine navy worsted, so - that would take quite a while to knit. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did she work after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Oh - her never stopped working until she was taken very ill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did she have any jobs?
