our when grandfather died but - they were always taken out and - and when my mother and - father - well I took on you see at fourteen - or thirteen and a half and - from that time on my mother's were taken out and took upstairs and - father's, and - accor
dingly. And after mother had died - father lived - fourteen years after her, ninety-four, his was always taken out first.
