 never asked for any. And - if mother could give me a ha'penny, which was - and the - the - the beauty of it was or the tragedy of it was - every child in the village, or most of them were in the same - in the same predicament because - there was - a fish
i
ng village, and - nearly everyone was on the fishing unless they had - their parents was - were market gardeners, and had some land, you see, so all my companions and friends - were the same as myself, you see, if there was good fishing with one boat well
 the majority of boats had the same, and if there was no fishing well it was the same for everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 What did you spend the money on when you got it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 We would go around the different shops in the village looking in the windows to see where we cou
ld have the most sweets. And there was one old lady called Mrs Arrol, or Miss Allow, and she sold Coopers Whispers. Excuse me. And I think we had about thirteen for a ha'penny. And - so I think that was what our happennies would be spent on - Saturday nig
hts. Then Toblers chocolates came in vogue, a penny bar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after her house and family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Nobody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 What about relations or friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Well if mother was sick - her - her sist
er would come in, or her nieces and help you know but otherwise - it was - her two daughters there, of course Ada was in the Post Office but Mary was always here to help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 What sort of things did they do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 They would - wash up the dishes and get the dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Would they clean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
And clean, yes, our - all our people here in the village could clean their houses I suppose every - every young person - could paper rooms and paint the rooms and because - my mother always did it, and - since time I
 was fourteen or - fourteen or fifteen I done the - the papering of the house, I could hang a piece of paper as good as anybody and paper a room and I could paint the room and - or I could line the ceilings and - there wasn't a thing I couldn't do in the 
house. And - most of the - the girls that was reared here in the village were brought up in that way.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did your mother and father have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes, mother had a sister. And - a brother. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did they see very much of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Oh yes. Yes, they were very close.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 At this house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
They - they - they both lived - close by. And my - my mother's brother, my uncle - his wife died - when he was - practically young - a young man, and his daughter, he lived with his dau
ghters they had and - they lived quite close and - he would spend lots of time here talking to father, as I said just now, politics and religion was always discussed - with three or four of the family, and - my father's brother was never married, and - he
 lived to be nearly eighty. And - he used to spend - most of his time in here. And so there was always plenty of - conversation and they were always very intelligent about - different topics of - of the day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 As opposed to just relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
Oh yes, father had - had a friends and he would speak about them and the roguery that they used to do when they were young. I wish I'd remembered all the stories he told me, but I'm afraid - I'm afraid I've forgotten them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did he see very much of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
Yes, but - one of two of his friends had gone away, gone to Wales, up in the mines to work, left the fishing you see and - and - one or two others had gone to America, and - so he never - he'd never see them a
nymore and - but he was always talk about the - the - good times he had when he was young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did your parents share the same friends?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Well she had - women friends of her own you see, which came to the house and - father's friends had gone away so
 he didn't have anybody but his brother that came - as regards his family, and his sister. He had a brother and sister who lived here, and he had several nieces, and they all came and were friendly and - mixed up with us you see, with - one another.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 When did he see them, did he go out to see them or did they come here to visit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
Oh they came here. They would come - here in the evenings and - mother's sister would come in - of a evening, especially if her husband was to sea and - they would do all 
- all their knitting, the sister-in-laws - around the fire. No - no lamp lit, it was only lamp in those days, and - the fire, and the flickering of the - coal, the fire, the flames, and they - the faster they knitted the faster they talked, you could - I 
c
an see them now, they - the steel needles, eight steel needles at each frock, the click click of the needles. I tell you what they would do - also they would - go over to Newlyn and buy the white cotton, the men would have the cotton to make the nets and 
h
ave them barked after, but the women would go over and have the cotton and they would make their curtains for the windows. Mesh - mesh the curtains and then darn a pattern in them, a flower pattern or something, so the - the short curtains they would make
 and some people had made}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1651909\charrsid3212931  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 long curtains. Used to look lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Were friends ever invited into the home, or did they just come as they felt like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No. They came in as they liked. No one was ever - specially invited in the family, not - not the co
usins or nieces or sisters, they always - took this house as the family house and it's still been that. When grandma and grandfather lived here}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1651909\charrsid3212931  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 all - all their family of - of sons and daughters came here you see and their - grandchildren, and even when the
y died it was still - they still did that. And - since my parents have died our family, my sisters and brothers and their nieces and nephews have taken - this home as their own you know and - seem to be the old family house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 When they came here were they given things to eat and to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Oh well, if sometimes - if we - if they were having a meal, mother would ask them to have a - a - cup of tea or anything and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 What about special occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No, any - any time in - any day, and - I can
 remember now - my cousins always coming in - if Aunt Lizzie had made any cakes they always said Aunt Lizzie's heavy cake was better than their own. And they'd like to have a pi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1651909\charrsid3212931 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 ce of mother's I think all children thought that, and we always thought somebody else was different to our own.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did your parents ever go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 My parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did they go out to visit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes. Oh yes, of a evening they would be invited out or sometimes they didn't - didn't want to be inv
ited, you just feel you would like to go to see your friends and you would go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
People often tell us that in those days they made their own amusements, what do you think your parents did when they got together with their friends and their neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
Well - they would - they would have a talk about the books they'd read - if they visited their neighbours and friends. But - our own amusements were - were made here in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 But when they went out did they ever sort of go out to make music or to play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
Many people divide society into different social classes or groups, in that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Well - I can't - say much about that because - he
re in this little community - it wasn't very much done you see. Apart from - the religious side of the question and the - politics, it was just them two things, and there was just the religious meetings or the - the politicians and - meetings one with the
 other and - going. There were no debates, no debating society or anything in that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you ever think of some people as being higher up the social ladder than yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Never. No. I never - I never thought that anyone was better than myself.
 And I can - look back now, a funny thing, a silly thing really, I can look back now as a child - coming home to school to dinner, coming home after dinner, coming home in the afternoon you know, and thinking when I got to our front door that it was the b
e
st door in Mousehole. And that is my opinion as a child, no one - no father was better than mine or mother, and I - I never thought that anyone was - better than me - money didn't me in my mind make anybody better, and - I - in my own opinion and - I'm gl
ad to say that I - never felt inferior to any body.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Nowadays we talk about the working class and the middle class and the upper class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 You don't think there was anything like this in Mousehole at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No, I don't think that - I know for one thing that my father would never think anybody better than him. And - he - he was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 What about people worse than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 He was intelligent, he read a lot and we all read and I think that that's a kind of - opened up our horizon an
d - took us to different countries - and all that but - in our - in our reading and our way of - books we read, my parents never believed in - in reading any trash, they always wanted to enlarge your memory and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did your father or you ever think that people were worse than yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 What sort of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
Well, even people here fishing that had the bigger families than us, had it hard pinch sometimes - to - to live, you know. And - no, we could always - have sympathy with th
e people that - we thought had hard times, although we had hard ourselves. But - it was a funny - life really, a funny thing to - think on now because - somehow - always something happened - and my father would say to me even when - when - he got old and 
I
 was young and married and still on the fishing and I would worry sometimes if the weeks was passing and the boats hadn't been to sea, and father would say, my child, don't worry, I've gone through it all, I've worried and everything had worked out. Well 
- and so don't - leave it there to time, and I think that - he was a great help to me in - that respect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Were you ever taught by your father and mother to sort of curtsey to anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 We were always told to be courteous and kind and I think that's
 how - there's so much delinquency now with the children because they're not taught in the home. You always - always had to respect old age and that was the hiding I had from my father that day, because I was disrespectful you see, which I never forgot.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 I said curtsey?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Oh - I'm sorry, yes, yes, take off your hat, yes. Always told that. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Who would you do that to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Well we always done it to - to anybody older than ourselves, and asked them if we - if we - were sitting in a - in a wag
onette when we were young - there were no buses then and - older per - person came in and there was hardly room for her we always got up, and sat on my parents lap or sat on - somebody else's lap you know to make room. Always asked to oblige and make room
 for old people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Was there anyone that you would call sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No. No, not in the village, no. Oh no, we were all the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Do you remember anyone calling your father sir or your mother madam at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No. No. We were of the working class, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 And everybody was working class there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Do you remember who was considered the most important people in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Well, the people who - who owned the post - owned boats and farms and that, it's a few - we
althy farmers around, but still - we didn't - we didn't - think that that they were any better than ourselves. They may have had money but they - they didn't seem to be that - brainy and - intellectual that you know, we didn't - we ne - we never thought -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
So if all the people were considered the same you got on with everybody in the village? Did you come into contact with people like shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Oh yes, we would have to for our groceries, where the Lobster Pot is now was our grocery shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 You didn't think of them as being better than yourselves,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 What about teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
Well we look up to teachers because they were - knowledgeable and they were - teaching us every day, but - we were all good friends one with the other and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you come into contact with teachers socially?
