Yes. Yes, that was - one of the great things in my young life, that - always worried me. And - when at school lots of times - my mind was not on
 my lessons but on my parents and - especially if there had been no fish for a long time, and thinking about my mother and - the hardship and the - worry that she had and also my father - which I think kind of - spoiled my school life, I think I was - a v
e
ry sensitive - a - a very sensitive child, and - those things were always on top - I would never ask for pocket money on a Saturday, we never had any, only on a Saturday, but if my father had - not been to sea and caught any fish I wouldn't ask for - anyt
hing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 What difference do you think it made if your father was ill or out of work?
