Well my father practically was a very strong man, and - luckily for him he didn't have much sickness, but - the - no one but fisher people - I don't think could eve
r have lived in the old days as they did. They were very thirty, as I said before, and very careful - on what they had, and because they had a few pounds one week they didn't waste it, they always looked out for a rainy day, and - I felt so often that - t
hey deserved medals.
