\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No. No, we never had any help from any - from anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 There was no Poor Relief?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No, never had it in our lives - when I was - sometimes 
in the winters - the - Mr Bolitho the - the Bolitho family were very - very good in there for - for making work, they would have - roads - roads - road making - in the country, and if there had been many - many - weeks or months of - of - of bad weather o
r
 no fish - our fishermen or - some of them would apply for a job, and - my father have - had worked lots of times in the slack season, by Mr Bolitho on road - making and different things, which my mother always thought was a - was a Godsend and - I think 
the last time he - he went on that job he - the - magnificent sum of eighteen shillings a week, which - my mother and him thought was - well was a Godsend.
