\insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 s ever being made of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes. Yes. Yes. Well - one was made, a - a - I don't know that my family done it but - some Americans - American co
uple came here to live years ago when I was a young woman and I'd had a very big illness, a burst ulcer, and I had been for - I suppose three months on a - milk diet, and these Americans came - a man and wife and - and - rented a house on the front - of t
h
e village, just around the corner from here, and my - daughter - came one day and said that I could - I could go and sit in the sun, and I hadn't been out for a long while, and - my mother helped me down - at the front there where the - the cottage that I
 
sat on the steps was my grandparents, and of course, they had been dead many years and - a relative was still living there, but the house that - these Americans lived in well they had to pass this cottage you see, I sat at - on the steps, and the - and a 
n
eighbour had bought a cushion for me, it was a very - very pleasant morning and the sun hot and - just after the first world war. So I was sitting there with my sister-in-law and - enjoying the sun and the work lady, the work woman, she was a Mousehole pe
r
son who was working for this American couple was coming out looking toward me, quite often and going back again, and I wondered whatever in the world she was doing. And - at last she came to me, and - she said - look, she said, Nettie, you must - you must
 
