e
 doesn't want to pass, so you must go and - go off this wharf. And then she'd come out, she's waiting to go to Penzance. Well, you know, I - I felt that I had it - I - I - I suppose I thought that - I hadn't been told what I had and I thought it was stoma
c
h and - anyway - I was very upset about this, and all the neighbourhood at that time was up in arms about it. Well I came off - the wharf and - my mother was indignant because she had been born there and - you know, she was very indignant about it. Well t
