No. I went to school when I was three. My sister was - going in for teaching at that time and - she would take me up - with her in the mornings and - I was always there when the bell was being run, they ha
d a - a school bell which - rang out at a quarter to - nine in the mornings and quarter to two - and - quarter past one in the afternoons to collect the children, all came home to dinner - at that time. But - I never had - only my - mother, she would - sh
e would make me do my homework in the nights and - for spelling and that and - of course I was always poring over books that I think I learnt to read very early.
