Well yes, that was instilled in us also, to always be - have towards elderly people with respect, see, and - to give up our seat to them - in a conveyance or anywhere where any old people had to stand for the young one to ge
t up, always show respect to the elderly, or the sick, and I - I've come to the conclusion that those things aren't - aren't - spoken of much in schools, not in this day, I - I think we got - most of our training in the schools and with our parents at tha
t time.
\par 
