 Now he had five sons you see, and himself would be six so he would only have to have - another man to make the crew, see. And - so unfortunately the war - came in and - this boat then had to be laid up until the war ended. Well that finished my husband' 
y
achting. Which he was sad - he was sorry about himself and - I was also, because - it was a different life then and - he liked - he liked yachting and going around like he - he had been all over - Europe and - different countries, and - then of course whe
n
 he came home in the yachts - to - to pay up the yacht the war started and as I said just now he - hadn't had a chance to come home for his clothes. And then from that time then he was sent - to Africa on the Kinton Castle. And - they were there about - I
 think about eighteen months.
