n
 a sack. Sacks of coal the sugar would be and - the lard would be in bladders, used to call a bladder lard, be in this - stiff greaseproof paper, all different sizes, I can hear still the cracking of the paper as the old shopkeeper cut her knife in throug
h
, and - weighed it, 'cos the - the butcher's lard would be in - in - she would run down her own lard for - what we call the butcher's lard, the best lard, she'd buy the - bacon - the pork and run it down, and that would be extra - good lard, cost more. So
 everything had to be weighed, except the tea, the tea all came in packets, four}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11608922\charrsid3212931  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 pence ha }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
