pence ha'penny a quarter, and - the sugar tuppence ha'penny a pound, or tuppence, and currants the same. And - all that stuff, flour had to be weighed. She had 
a big - big scales in the back of the shop, and - it would be from a pound to twenty pound being weighed. All according if you had the - big family, take twenty pound to put you over the weekend and making bread and cake, and different things, because eve
rybody then made their own bread. Very few had bought bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did the children ever go out with just their father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Go out with their father? Oh - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 They never went out with him by himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes, and as I was sick, if I was sick they wo
uld go out with their father, but - any other time you know if - if Jack was home - over a weekend we would go out together, with the children, Saturdays or Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Do you remember doing anything special on Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Bank Holidays - would 
be perhaps, if the weather was fine we'd go to St Ives. St Ives would be a treat in those days. We'd go by train. No - no buses when the children were young.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you walk to Penzance then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes, sometimes we did, yes, or go - in the wagonette or - other times you'd have to walk. And - go to St Ives or Car}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11608922\charrsid3212931 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 lli}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11608922\charrsid3212931 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 s Bay.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 What would you do when you got there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Sit on the sand and go bathing and - if the weather was fine enough. Well we'd go to Lemorna in the spring of the year before the - su
n came on hot, we used to go walk to Lemorna and back, especially on Good Friday, Easter time was - flocks of people would go there. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you ever go away for a holiday with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Never had a holiday with the children. Go away for th
e day perhaps, Plymouth sometimes with them, of a Saturday. Navy week or something on special. But - never had a - a - a holiday all together in our lives. And when I went to London with Sylvia to stay with my cousin, my husband couldn't - he said he coul
dn't be spared from the boat, and he didn't go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 How did you spend Saturdays in those days when you had the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Well we were busy up to dinner time finishing up the work and - Saturday mornings we'd be getting the dinner and - finishing the 
work we hadn't done - everything had to be scrubbed and polished and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11608922\charrsid3212931 as we said shining like dagger}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
, and - then in the afternoon, if it was fine we'd go for a walk, and - I may go visiting or Penzance, children would have their clothes changed, they'd be
 off - maybe - football, that was the - that had started then in the village, football team you see, after the - after the first world war, and after that time we didn't have any football, and - everyone then would flock to the - Upper Guin}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11608922\charrsid3212931 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 ess where the f
ootball match was being held, and of course they were too young to go on their own and - and Jack'd want to go off with the men and sometimes - they would go with their father, and - other times I would take them. And that was - every Saturday afternoon i
n the wintertime. The time the football started.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 What about Saturday night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Mm. Saturday evening? Oh, in - reading, or having their games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Were Sundays different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No. Yes, oh - quite different Sundays were, there'd be church mornings a
nd Sunday school in the afternoons and church again in the evening, and then in the evening after church they would have a book, if we didn't go out visiting our friends or relations - they always loved visiting or someone coming in here in the nights, an
d - Sunday evenings they could have a book, but never had any toys.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 This is when your children were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you think it was wrong to work or to enjoy yourself on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Well we were brought up in that at - that narrow wa
y that - I - I never done it myself, I never - washed or - didn't sew a button on of a Sunday, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 You continued that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 The children - yes, we didn't allow the children to - any - their - or not too much playing around. Never went out in th
e road to play, never allowed to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you have clean clothes on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes. But we always put our under clothes clean Saturdays. After a good old wash and - change Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Were there children allowed to play games on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Not rough games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 What about things like snakes and ladders?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
No. No, never played any - any - board games, snakes and ladders or - and - even now the children say to me, grandchildren, shall we have a game of snap? I say, no, not today, it's Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 You went to chapel on Sundays didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 How often did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
Well I know you'll laugh because no one - no one wouldn't do it now, we've had a class - our - class meetings was always Sunday mornings before the - ser
vice. And - a lady, Mrs Evan Tregensa, she took our class for years. And - we all turned out on Sunday morning and we would - go from there into the church for the service. And then after that we'd come in and have our dinner and half past two was Sunday 
- quarter to three was Sunday school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
Yes. And - up - up to the time I was married until I was - when I - when I was going to have my first child I went. And - went to Sunday school in the afternoons and church again in the evenings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did Jack go along too when you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No. No. He never went with me. He attended a different church to I, when he was young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Which one was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 He attended the - the - United Methodist church at the other end of the village. Now it's amalgamated into one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 This was the same chapel you went to when you were younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Were you a member of the temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes. Band of Hope we called it. Yes, Band of Hope. I played for them when I was
 - well perhaps eleven or twelve, I - I was asked to play for them and - and then when I got - a bit older I was secretary, I've still got the old books here - with the boys names on it, promising to keep the pledge, singing their names, how many of them 
- were - were killed in the first world war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you belong to any other club after you were married that were affiliated to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Oh no, Wesley Guild that was affiliated to the chapel, and - the Band of Hope we as the chapel and - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did your children go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes. Until the war years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you ever take them to chapel, with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes, they always went with us.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Just you or with Jack as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 My husband in the evenings, he went - always went in 
the evenings and the children went - in the mornings as well, and - be four of us in the evenings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 When you had the children here did you say grace at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No. No, we never said - never said grace at meals, I don't know for why but - it was ne
ver started, and - I'm afraid my parents didn't for us and I suppose that's - that's the reason that I didn't do it. But - my grandparents - did. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No. Never had family prayers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Were your children taught to say prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
Yes, every night they had a - a prayer. They never went to bed unless they said their prayers and asked - the Lord to help all that was sick or sorry and they would - go off sometimes without being told anything you know, raking up everyth
ing under the sun.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Who taught them, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes, no I taught them their prayers, Gentle Jesus meek and mild was the - first prayer that they were told.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 How long did they keep saying prayers for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Well they were big - big boys you know when they - they - then they wanted to say their prayers to theirselves and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 But before that did they actually say them aloud to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you take an interest in politics after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Always did - politics, we a
re always - we were brought up - to think on politics - as one of the essential things you know. And I'm afraid - this latter years I don't take the interest that I did take.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 But at that time what were your political views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Well we were Liberals, and that was what we always - voted, and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Was your husband politically interested?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 He was Liberal. He was Liberal in his politics, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you vote in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Do you remember what year it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 I couldn't say now, no, I don't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did your husband vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Do you know what party he voted for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Liberal, he was always very - Liberal minded.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you or your husband ever feel any pressure from anybody to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
No, I never tried to inflict my - my opinion on him. He always pleased himself I don't think that he was a man that would - change for anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 But were you pressurized from somebody outside the family at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No. No. Everybody was allowed to please themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Were you actually a member of the Liberal party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Were you a paid up member?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes. We didn't pay in our Liberal party, because - Sir Clifford Corey was our - our - our - our member for 
very many years, he was a very wealthy man, he had - he owned lots of - coalmines and that in Wales, and - he built or had built the Liberal room, and - he fitted it all out, what was required and we had a women's room upstairs and - we had a - our monthl
y meetings, the same as - well - the men was there every night or every day with their papers and that provided.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 After you were married did you ever work for any of the parties at elections?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 I used to help - on elections.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 What sort of things would you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
I would be in the room and - and check up the votes that were being brought in. Or you could go and see anybody that was sick and not able to - go themselves and help them or - try and get a conveyance for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did your husband ever do that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No. He was always too busy. Lots - lots of elections he wasn't home to vote so - he was away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you take part in any political activity at any other time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Not just election times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Concerts and 
that we would - we would do to help out the - get some funds of our own and that. And then we would get up the concerts in the - middle of the season. We'd have a - a special evening and at that time in the village there would be - I suppose it was a Libe
ral village, quite different to now with all the - locals dead and - moving away from the village and visitors coming in, you don't know now who the visitors, what they are or - no, or how they vote.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 When you and your husband were not working how did you spend your time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
Well, we would be - we - I don't know when my husband wasn't working because with all the boat's - gear to - to get ready - even if they were in from sea in poor weather there were always things that he had to do. And see about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you ever go out together in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 What sort of thing did you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
Well we had that - we had - not all that to go to, we just went out for a walk in the evening or went visiting. And - seeing friends. We didn't have al
l that money to spare to go to - any - big does or - concerts - that - was taking part - taking place in Penzance. I don't think we - we went there very often. But - we could always go for a walk or - amuse ourselves with the children, take the children o
u
t somewhere and - on the beach in the summer if there was any time - to spare. And I'll tell you what we - we did very often, Jack would go out in a - in a boat, little boat, the punt, small boat and take us out and the children and - we've had lots of pi
c
nics on the island when we were - when the children were younger. And - different places, you see, go away with - and in the boat. Boats used to go away at that time, when the children were small, what they called trouting. They'd go across the bay to Por
t
 Levin, or Mullion, and - we've done that several times in the summer. Would be quite a lot of people then, have a nice - lot of - our friends would go with us, and we'd tale our food, and - have it on the boat. Land at Port Levin, especially at St Peters
 time when there was a special weekend for galas and - big does down there. So - in the old days or when we were young or our children were young there was lots of boating done, more so than - is done now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Was your husband ever working so that he would get home every evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
No, he didn't - he never done anything but - the - the fishing, and then at certain times of the year, pilchard driving, that was in the summertime they would be in perhaps about ten, eleven o'clock or twelve or one, but never early in the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 When he was home, presumably he was home sometimes early in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes, i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15207351\charrsid3212931 f he was lin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 ing, if they were out for two or three days lining. That's - they would be in perhaps in the afternoon to land their fish, which 
would be turbot, ray, ling, white fish, and - then - after being out two or three days they might land on the Wednesday afternoon and be in that evening. Then the Thursday morning they would go to sea again, for a couple of days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 What sort of things would he do in the evenings when he was in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Read. Or - if the children was young amuse the children. And - that would be much - as much as he would do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did he ever go out to any clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Not very often. Not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Which one would he go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Well the Liberal Club would be here but }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15207351\charrsid3212931 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931  Jack}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15207351\charrsid3212931  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 was - it's - it's many years since Jack went to any clubs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did he ever go to pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 What about institutes of any sort?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No, he never went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you go together ever to the clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 You always stayed at home did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you belong to any savings clubs when you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Savings clubs? No, not - particularly, the bazaar club at our - our church bazaar we paid in - thrift you know to
 pick up anything at the end of the year but - not - any club we never paid in for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did either of you take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Perhaps like cricket or football?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Or fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No. Oh yes, fishing, the boys - the boys - 
took part in football when they got older. But we never had a cricket match here in the village. No, it's a funny thing, Pool, the little village above us here, they always had a cricket club, but we never did. Mm. Yes, a good job too or there'd be fricti
on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you ever go bicycling together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No, I never rode a bicycle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you ever bet on anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No, I never bet in my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 What about Jack?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No, he didn't very often. You know, he always he said he missed his chance one ye
ar because his birthday came on April the fifth, his birthday is April the fifth I should say, and - he was fishing at the time and when he got into the market Saturday - or Friday, the men were putting - some men putting their money on different horses, 
a
nd - I think someone said to him, aren't you going to put a horse on April the fifth? And - being not accustomed to doing it he didn't. And that horse came in first next day and - I think some odd - it was a lot of money but he always said he missed his c
hance.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Do you think he ever bet apart from that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
No. No, never bet on horses or anything. I tell you they had some - they had some - little money that they was always afraid to - to waste any of it. Very careful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 When you were married did you go to theatres or concerts, music halls, that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
No. You see we were three mile from Penzance and we didn't have anything like that happen here. Might have a concert once in a while, we'd go to a concert. But never went to Penzance to theatricals after we were married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 When did the cinema come to Penzance, did you ever go to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
Yes. Oh yes. Yes. Yes. When we went together first - the winter, that winter - and - as I said before Jack went for yachting early in the spring. H
e was made Quartermaster - on the - on the yacht that he was on - two or three years before we were married, and he was hoping to have made that his - job in life, yachting you know and - if it hadn't been for the boat that his father had bought, but - he
 - we went to the cinema, we used to - walk - forth and back, three mile - never thought anything about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Jack? No. No, well I had hobbies and crochet, I could crochet or - knit, things like that you know. Loads of dif
ferent things - in the house, but not to - I never done rug making.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you ever keep pets of any sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
No. We did have a dog and I'm sorry, we had a little dog when - the children when the boys were young, they wanted a dog and we had a dog for quite a few years, when they were young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you have a garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 A small garden at the back.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes, we've still got the small garden at the back of the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you ever collect anything as a sort of hobby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No, I never collected stamps, only for the children. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 What about for yourself, did you ever collect anything for yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you ever go out to enjoy yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Well we did because - in later - well there was choir practic
e which I enjoyed very much when I was young. I think I said before we were all - I was out most nights when I was young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 What about when you were married though, did you go out to do things that you enjoyed when you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Well I - I did
 until I was - I had Jack, six months - with Jack and then I - I finished with the male voice then. And - I couldn't - take an anything more after that then of course I had the other - had Bill quickly after Jack. I had no time to do that kind of thing, n
o
t be tied down - every - Monday night for practice. And - I've been asked - to - today to - had a letter today to ask me to be vice-president of the male voice choir, which was very nice. But - apart from - male voice I went to - help - in concerts after 
I was married, and - bazaar - opened bazaars at the church and different things. And I went in the choir for many years after I was married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did anyone outside the home help you look after the house and family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No, not very many. I would have lik
ed lots of times when my parents - got old for somebody to have - helped me to have gone out for a few evenings - you know, to - been a break for me, but I had my parents all the day and - mother was in a bed there, eighteen months before she died and fat
her was in a bed - nearly that - eighteen months before he died, but - I had not chance of - going out very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you ever have anybody in to do any housework at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes. I had to have help for - lots of times when - mother and father were i
ll - to do the wash - help me with the washing, because we washed down in the basement, see, and I should be up and down two flights of stairs, and - I got very run down at one time, and we had a young woman to come in every Monday then to help me for - u
ntil she got married, two or three years after, she got married. But - you know I washed - I done all of me own work periodically, it was just - at times when I was sick that I had to have help.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 How did the family manage when you were in bed sick?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
Well my husband would get the food. If he was home. And - if I didn't my sister would - she was around - she went to live in Plymouth - for many years after but - or a neighbour would come in, my sister-in-law sometimes used to come down and - give me a
 cup of tea or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you have lots of relatives living near?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
No, a very small family. My sister was here, me only sister, it was the second sister went to America, and my eldest brother went to America and - they both died there, and - m
y sister was the - was the only person here until - perhaps about ten years before father died she went to Plymouth to live, so I was here on my own and I - had - only one or two first cousins - here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you have friends as opposed to relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 I - we'd lots of friends in the village, always had lots of friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Where did you see them in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Well they would come down perhaps of a evening to see me, or call in of a afternoon. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you and Jack share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
He had his men friends you know, I don't know that his friends were the same as mine. He mixed with you know - seafaring men and men he met on the yachts and that. It's - he - he had a big family, Jack, he had a sister - his mother had the - another
 sister and two or three brothers and he was - he had more relatives than what I had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Where did he meet his friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Oh out in the - on the - on the cliff if they were out walking or that sometimes they'd come in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Were friends ever invited here?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes, they - they didn't want to be invited, this is open house for anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 How often would you friends come?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Oh well, pretty often, they used to call in different times, there was no - phoning to ask could they come in those days, 
in fact we'd - we never had a phone in the village, and - they just called in casually to see us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you give them things to eat and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Well we always had a cup of tea ready for our friends}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15207351\charrsid3212931 
, and still do if they come. Kettle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931  is on - and call in any odd time of the day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Would they come on particular days or particular occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No. No, just any time - afternoons generally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Would you say that the friends invited in were your friends or your husband's friends or perhaps both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
Well I had more friends than me husband who came in casually you know, his friends would be working - people, working men and - would only call in the evenings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you ever go out to visit your friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 By yourself or with Jack?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
Yes. Go out of a odd evening if we - if we had - a few minutes to spare with the children gone to bed and - we'd go out and visit our - relatives - relations or friends for a little while.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you make music when you went to visit or play games with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
Oh yes, we had music, I'd play the piano in lots of houses if we went in and - had a sing-song, that was the - I think the most of our en - entertainments in the evening was singing the old songs, and - I could always - play 
impromptu, I - I could play by ear what they - say you know, without the music, if I heard anything once I could always - rattle it off on the piano after. So we'd have lots of fun when we were younger in - singing off the old pieces and - you could tell 
a song in those days, you could play it off, it's a hard job now to know what they're singing and - I'm sure I would never be able to play them. Don't seem any beginning or end.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you play any games with the people you went to visit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Yes. In the wintertime. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 What games would you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
Well, different games - I don't know whether you've never heard of the games, boots without the spurs, and - which was very laughable, we had lots of fun over that. And - blindfolding - somebody - an
d - giving them a target before they had a - a handkerchief put over their eyes and - something on the walk they had to - think you could - walk straight with your finger out like that you see and you'd put them in the right direction and then you'd be th
e
re waiting for them to come and try and put their finger and you would just - have your mouth ready to give their finger a snap. Oh we had lots of fun, with silly old games like that you know, and - but they caused a lot of amusement in those days, and we
 had to make our own amusement. We didn't have it made - made for us like we do now and television, different things. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Do you think on the whole that you had to struggle to make ends meet in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Oh yes, our - our lives were one hard struggle in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 What did you think about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 
In looking back - in retrospect on - on my life and on our - our way of living I don't know how we managed, honestly, I think very often don't know what the young wives - now - would do, if th
ey had the same money as we had - in fact we never knew from one week to the other - what we would have to spend - on the fishing we lived on faith. And - I think lots of times that we done a marvellous job, and our children, we tried to - do - I never to
l
d our children whether we had much or little. I never worried them like I had been worried when I was young. I always - always - made up my mind on that lot that - I would never tell the children, to bother their little minds like mine was, I was a very s
ensitive child I think and - I worried a lot of my young life away thinking about my father and - what was happening if there was no fish, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 What difference did it make if your husband was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Well, if he happened to be ill and the boat was 
fishing he would always have his share - of the - fish that was caught you see because his nets - he had his own gear on the boat, each man had their own, then the - four brothers on the boat had the - had the nets for the family you see that they had the
ir share. And - then if - when the National Health - was passed that benefit came in - if you had a doctor you would have so much from the doctor, see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6429687 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 Did you ever get help from the parish or a charity or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2506258 NP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14897221\charrsid3212931 No, I never had any help in my life. What my husband never got I didn't get my - I never had.
\par }}